'''Aargau: For All Your Banking Needs''' was a series of ''[[Planet Hoppers]]'' articles from [[August]] [[2003]], covering the planet [[Aargau/Legends|Aargau]] and other characters and settings appearing in [[Marvel Comics]]' [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'' series]]. The articles were written by [[Cory J. Herndon]] and published by [[Wizards of the Coast]] on [[Wizards.com]] as a supplement for the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''.

==Contents==
===Part 1: Three Simple Laws===
''&hellip;a seasoned customs agent advises a newcomer on the statutes of [[Aargau/Legends|Aargau]] (and where to find a decent [[Bantha steak/Legends|bantha steak]]).''<ref name="Aargau" />

===Part 2: Secure Lines of Credit===
''&hellip;a senior customs agent trains a new recruit on the security [[holoscanner]], which keeps anyone from leaving Aargau with more than they brought in.''<ref name="Aargau" />

===Part 3: Now 99% Crime Free===
''&hellip;Sergeant [[Rolex]] helps catch a [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] working for [[Li-Suun Niik]], the biggest and most elusive criminal on Aargau.''<ref name="Aargau" />

===Part 4: Checks, Balances, and Overdrafts===
''&hellip;Princess Leia and Darth Vader completely miss the point of Aargau's annual "[[Take Your Daughter to Work Day]]".''<ref name="Aargau" />

